1
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,633
Siwoo.

2
00:00:08,967 --> 00:00:10,719
Kim Siwoo.

3
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:14,264
Stop drinking if you're drunk.

4
00:00:14,264 --> 00:00:16,641
Doesn't it exhaust you, drinking like this every time?

5
00:00:16,766 --> 00:00:20,520
How would someone who can't even drink know this fun?

6
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:21,730
And,

7
00:00:22,439 --> 00:00:23,815
if you're just going to sip on soda,

8
00:00:23,815 --> 00:00:26,151
why are you even here?

9
00:00:26,151 --> 00:00:28,737
Take a look around.

10
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:30,321
The only person drinking soda here...

11
00:00:30,321 --> 00:00:32,323
...is probably you.

12
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:37,787
I'm not telling you not to drink.

13
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:40,165
I'm just saying you should pace yourself.

14
00:00:58,516 --> 00:00:59,851
What.

15
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:06,733
But I like that you don't drink.

16
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:08,651
What?

17
00:01:10,111 --> 00:01:14,741
If you get drunk, who's going to take care of me?

18
00:01:19,537 --> 00:01:23,708
The only person who'd pick me up when I'm passed out on the street,

19
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:26,002
and stay by my side till the very end while I drink,

20
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:27,629
is you.

21
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:33,802
That's why I can let go and get drunk around you.

22
00:01:36,471 --> 00:01:38,264
Is that why you drink like there's no tomorrow?

23
00:01:39,641 --> 00:01:40,892
Yeah.

24
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:44,270
It means I trust you that much.

25
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:52,570
But you should never drink.

26
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:56,783
I really don't want to die of a heart attack.

27
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:22,559
Hey, are you crazy?

28
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,602
Hey... a senior...

29
00:02:24,602 --> 00:02:27,730
How could I refuse when a senior offered it?

30
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:31,192
Hey, even so!

31
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:34,070
Hey, Siwoo.

32
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:36,990
Hey, wake up!

33
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,283
Hey!

34
00:02:38,283 --> 00:02:39,325
Breathe!

35
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:42,662
Excuse me, senior!

36
00:02:42,662 --> 00:02:43,538
Please call an ambulance!

37
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:45,290
Please, someone call an ambulance!

38
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,041
Hey, wake up!

39
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:49,127
Please?

40
00:02:52,046 --> 00:02:55,758
Hey, wake up.

41
00:02:57,552 --> 00:03:00,013
Never drink again.

42
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:03,391
Because there's no one else who takes care of me like you do.

43
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:06,144
Does that even make sense?

44
00:03:07,020 --> 00:03:11,524
Hey, it's a compliment. A compliment.

45
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:13,610
Where else could I find someone

46
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:15,653
who understands everything I do as much as you?

47
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,865
Even a girlfriend wouldn't be able to do this much.

48
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:21,618
How lucky am I?

49
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:25,455
If you were my girlfriend, you would've run away ages ago.

50
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:29,792
But since we're friends, you're staying by my side.

51
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:31,336
Siwoo.

52
00:03:31,336 --> 00:03:34,088
Drink soda next to me for the rest of your life.

53
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:40,094
If you're going to keep drinking, I'm leaving first.

54
00:03:41,554 --> 00:03:43,014
I'll pay the bill,

55
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:45,183
so find your own way home.

56
00:03:50,355 --> 00:03:51,564
Hey.

57
00:03:51,564 --> 00:03:53,608
Kim Siwoo.

58
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:55,276
Hey!

59
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:04,953
How lucky am I?

60
00:04:04,953 --> 00:04:08,498
If you were my girlfriend, you would've run away ages ago...

61
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:13,253
Lucky that we're friends?

62
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:15,755
Do I have to remain just a friend

63
00:04:15,755 --> 00:04:18,341
to stay by your side?

64
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:21,219
You're leaving alone? How mean.

65
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:22,428
Let's go together.

66
00:04:22,428 --> 00:04:24,264
You're heavy.

67
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:27,809
Siwoo.

68
00:04:27,809 --> 00:04:30,937
I'm too drunk to walk.

69
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:32,939
You walked here just fine.

70
00:04:32,939 --> 00:04:34,983
You've been a bit cold lately.

71
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:36,693
What are you talking about?

72
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:40,280
I mean, I was wondering if it's because of what Cha Dojin said today.

73
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,407
Just wondering.

74
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:47,495
Aren't you guys sick of sticking together every single day?

75
00:04:47,495 --> 00:04:51,291
The juniors were asking me if you two are dating.

76
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:54,252
Are you guys actually dating?

77
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:58,172
Is this the first time Cha Dojin spouted nonsense?

78
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:05,513
I was thinking about it earlier while smoking.

79
00:05:05,513 --> 00:05:08,141
What if you really do have feelings for me?

80
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:09,309
That's what I thought about.

81
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:13,146
What is it that you want to say?

82
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,523
That you actually believe that nonsense about me liking you?

83
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:19,819
No, I just said I thought about it.

84
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:25,992
What if it's true?

85
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:28,328
If it is true, then what?

86
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:29,787
Does it gross you out?

87
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:32,248
Think you could never see my face again?

88
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:36,085
No.

89
00:05:36,085 --> 00:05:38,171
"I should treat you even better."

90
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,922
That's the conclusion I came to.

91
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:41,507
What?

92
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:46,471
If you really do like me,

93
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,681
you'll probably avoid me after confessing your feelings.

94
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:53,061
I mean, it's like that in dramas too.

95
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:54,854
Once your feelings are caught, you either run away,

96
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:56,814
or drift apart.

97
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:59,525
I don't want that to happen.

98
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:03,237
So I'm going to treat you even better.

99
00:06:03,237 --> 00:06:05,114
I'll make you want to stay by my side forever,

100
00:06:05,114 --> 00:06:06,699
so you won't even think about confessing.

101
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:11,788
I won't let my feelings show, so we won't drift apart.

102
00:06:11,996 --> 00:06:16,751
Besides, I get bored without you.

103
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:31,349
You selfish jerk.

104
00:06:34,377 --> 00:06:39,019
A few days later

105
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:57,542
I'm not drunk.

106
00:06:58,334 --> 00:06:59,710
See?

107
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,838
I told you to go easy on the drinks.

108
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:04,674
Move.

109
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:11,180
Siwoo.

110
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:15,435
What would I do without you?

111
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:19,021
Stop talking nonsense and go inside.

112
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,773
I'm leaving.

113
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:25,278
Have some hangover soup before you go.

114
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:29,407
Oh right, you didn't drink.

115
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,535
Wanna stay for some ramen?

116
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:33,369
I'm good.

117
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:37,039
We have a first-period class tomorrow.

118
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:38,541
Wash up and go to sleep.

119
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:39,500
Don't be late tomorrow.

120
00:07:40,835 --> 00:07:44,088
Always nagging.

121
00:07:44,088 --> 00:07:45,840
Thanks for today.

122
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,551
Get home safe.

123
00:07:57,351 --> 00:08:00,480
I think I know how you feel,

124
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:02,523
and I know you'd reject me,

125
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:09,989
but what am I supposed to do when I can't give up?

126
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:12,408
Why did it have to be you?

127
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:35,556
I'm not supposed to waver.

128
00:08:35,556 --> 00:08:42,146
I really don't want to lose you.

129
00:08:42,146 --> 00:08:48,152
I want you by my side for the rest of my life.

130
00:08:48,152 --> 00:08:56,285
But our relationship isn't supposed to change.

131
00:08:56,285 --> 00:09:01,666
I guess it's right for me to keep pretending not to know, right?

132
00:09:04,085 --> 00:09:08,172
If you knew I felt this way about you...

133
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:14,303
...how would you react?
